Key Match Events: Giannis Antetokounmpo posted his fourth triple-double of the season with 11 points, 12 rebounds, and 13 assists.
Damian Lillard scored 25 points to lead the Milwaukee Bucks to a 128-104 victory over the Toronto Raptors.
Giannis Antetokounmpo suffered a cut on his right little finger requiring stitches but continued to play.
Post-Match Reflections: Bucks coach Doc Rivers praised Antetokounmpo's passing, stating it set the tone for the team.
Rivers mentioned that when the best player passes well, it becomes contagious and the ball movement improves.
